===Noun===
'''pneumonoultramicroscopicsilicovolcanoconiosis''' (''plural'' '''pneumonoultramicroscopicsilicovolcanoconioses''')

#A hypothetical, invented [[disease]] of the lungs, caused by inhaling mineral or metallic dust, such as [[silicon]] and [[quartzite]], over a long [[period]].  

====Usage note====
This word was invented purely as a contender for the longest word in the English language and has 45 letters.  The word is not in official medical usage, and textbooks refer to this disease as [[pneumonoconiosis]], [[pneumoconiosis]] or [[silicosis]].

